  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 10 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 2 critical, 8 high, 5 medium, 24 normal. Key bases needing attention include Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI), Rome–Fiumicino Leonardo da Vinci (FCO/LIRF) and Larnaca (LCA/LCLK); plus 7 other bases. 5 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is thunderstorm / convective risk and mist  — most notably around David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO), Larnaca (LCA/LCLK) and Milan Malpensa (MXP/LIMC). Network hotspots: Göteborg Landvetter (GOT/ESGG), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Castellón-Costa Azahar (CDT/LECH), David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO) and 5 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, mist and approach minima limits. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Göteborg Landvetter (GOT/ESGG), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Castellón-Costa Azahar (CDT/LECH) and 9 others.",
